Energy Ministers from South Africa, Uganda, Sierra Leone, Liberia and Democratic Republic of Congo are among lead participants in the Powering Africa: Summit in Washington, DC. Others taking part in the two-day event include 400 investors and 50 speakers exploring global opportunities within Africa's energy & infrastructure sectors.&nbsp;Maintaining US competitiveness in Africa will be a key theme, setting out how commercial partnerships can deliver energy, create jobs, build capacity and spur industrial growth. Read more.&nbsp;